## 4. How Each Component Works

### 4.1 Configuration вҖ” [config.py](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/config.py)

Uses a frozen `@dataclass` to load secrets from [.env](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/.env) at startup:

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `WHATSAPP_TOKEN` | Meta access token for sending messages |
| `WHATSAPP_PHONE_NUMBER_ID` | Your WhatsApp Business phone ID |
| `WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN` | Secret for Meta webhook verification |
| `OPENROUTER_API_KEY` | API key for AI responses via OpenRouter |

Also provides computed properties [wa_messages_url](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/config.py#25-28) and [wa_headers](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/config.py#29-35) for convenient API calls.

---

### 4.2 App Entry Point вҖ” [main.py](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/main.py)

- Creates the FastAPI application with metadata (title, description, version)
- On startup: creates all database tables via `Base.metadata.create_all()`
- Includes the webhook router
- Provides a health check at `GET /`

---

### 4.3 Database вҖ” [database.py](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/database.py) + [models.py](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/models.py)

**Engine:** SQLite file ([sanmati.db](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/sanmati.db)), created automatically on first run.

**Tables:**

```mermaid
erDiagram
    STUDENTS {
        int id PK
        string name
        string phone UK
        string exam_type
        string language
        boolean is_hot_lead
        datetime created_at
        datetime updated_at
    }
    INTERACTIONS {
        int id PK
        int student_id FK
        string message_direction
        text message_body
        string message_type
        datetime timestamp
    }
    STUDENTS ||--o{ INTERACTIONS : "has many"
```

- **Students:** Tracks every unique phone number that contacts the bot. Stores name, phone, exam type, language preference, and hot lead status.
- **Interactions:** Logs every single message (inbound AND outbound) with direction, body, and type.

---

### 4.4 Webhook Handler вҖ” [webhook.py](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/routers/webhook.py)

This is the **core brain** of the bot. It handles two endpoints:

#### `GET /webhook` вҖ” Meta Verification
When you configure the webhook URL in Meta Developer Portal, Meta sends a GET request with `hub.mode`, `hub.verify_token`, and `hub.challenge`. The server checks the token and returns the challenge as a `PlainTextResponse`.

#### `POST /webhook` вҖ” Incoming Messages
This is the main message processing pipeline:

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["POST /webhook<br>payload received"] --> B["Extract phone, text,<br>sender name"]
    B --> C{Has message?}
    C -->|No| D["Return 'ignored'<br>(status update)"]
    C -->|Yes| E["Get/Create Student<br>in database"]
    E --> F["Log inbound<br>interaction"]
    F --> G["Check hot lead<br>keywords"]
    G --> H{Message routing}
    H -->|"1, 2, or 3"| I["Send menu info<br>(template вҶ’ fallback text)"]
    H -->|"hi/hello/menu"| J["Send welcome<br>message"]
    H -->|"anything else"| K["Send to OpenRouter AI<br>for smart reply"]
    I --> L["Log outbound<br>interaction"]
    J --> L
    K --> L
    L --> M["Return 'processed'"]
```

**Message Routing Rules:**
| User Input | Bot Action |
|-----------|-----------|
| `1` | Engineering Programs info (fees, seats, branches) |
| `2` | ITI Courses info (trades, duration, fees) |
| `3` | Nursing Programs info (B.Sc, GNM, ANM) |
| `hi`, `hello`, `hey`, [start](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/main.py#38-44), `menu` | Welcome message with quick menu |
| Any other text | OpenRouter AI answers based on knowledge.txt |

---

### 4.5 WhatsApp Service вҖ” [whatsapp.py](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/services/whatsapp.py)

Two async functions that make direct HTTP calls to Meta's WhatsApp Cloud API:

- **[send_text_message(phone, text)](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/services/whatsapp.py#14-47)** вҖ” Sends a plain text message
- **[send_template_message(phone, template_name)](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/services/whatsapp.py#49-95)** вҖ” Sends a pre-approved template (with fallback to text if template doesn't exist)

Both use `httpx.AsyncClient` for non-blocking HTTP calls and log errors if the API returns a non-200 status.

---

### 4.6 AI Brain вҖ” [gemini.py](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/services/gemini.py)

Despite the filename, this now uses **OpenRouter** (via the OpenAI SDK):

1. **Loads** [knowledge.txt](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/knowledge.txt) at startup вҖ” a comprehensive document with all college info (programs, fees, placements, campus, admission process, contacts)
2. **Constructs a system prompt** that instructs the AI to act as an admission counselor and answer ONLY from the knowledge base
3. **Model:** `stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free` via OpenRouter
4. **Temperature:** `0.3` (low creativity for factual answers)
5. **Fallback:** If the API fails, returns a polite error message with the helpline number

---

### 4.7 Hot Lead Detection вҖ” [lead_detector.py](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/services/lead_detector.py)

Scans every incoming message for **high-intent keywords**:

```
fees, admission, placement, seat, apply, hostel, scholarship,
cutoff, last date, deadline, merit, counselling
```

Uses a pre-compiled regex for efficient matching. When detected, the student's `is_hot_lead` flag is set to `True` in the database вҖ” useful for prioritizing follow-ups.

---

### 4.8 Broadcast Tool вҖ” [broadcast.py](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/broadcast.py)

A standalone CLI script for bulk marketing:

```bash
python broadcast.py --file students.csv --template admission_welcome --batch-size 50
```

**Features:**
- Reads student data from CSV or Excel (requires a `phone` column)
- Sends WhatsApp template messages in rate-limited batches
- Default: 100 messages per batch, 1-hour delay between batches
- 0.5-second delay between individual messages
- Logs success/failure counts with a final summary

---

### 4.9 Message Payload Extraction вҖ” [helpers.py](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/app/utils/helpers.py)

Parses Meta's nested webhook JSON payload to extract:
- **Phone number** (`from` field)
- **Message text** (`text.body`)
- **Sender name** (`contacts[0].profile.name`)

Gracefully returns [(None, None, None)](file:///c:/Users/bhave/OneDrive/Desktop/sanmati%20bot/broadcast.py#166-207) for non-message payloads (like delivery status updates).

---

## 5. Data Flow вҖ” End to End

Here's what happens when a student sends "What are the fees for CSE?" on WhatsApp:

1. **Student** sends message on WhatsApp to the business number
2. **Meta** receives it and POSTs the webhook payload to `https://neumic-fistic-elin.ngrok-free.dev/webhook`
3. **ngrok** tunnels the request to `localhost:8000`
4. **FastAPI** receives the POST, extracts phone/text/name
5. **Database** creates or retrieves the student record
6. **Inbound interaction** is logged
7. **Hot lead detector** scans for keywords вҖ” "fees" is found вҶ’ student marked as рҹ”Ҙ hot lead
8. **Message router** sees it's free text вҶ’ sends to OpenRouter AI
9. **OpenRouter** generates a response using the knowledge base (CSE fees = вӮ№75,000/yr)
10. **WhatsApp service** sends the AI reply back via Meta API
11. **Outbound interaction** is logged
12. **Student** receives the answer on WhatsApp

